comment: I love your videos and have great respect for your research. The HADD hypothesis sounds completely wrong to me. I like your comment about religion being social obligation but thought one of your older videos argued against this? It seems some of the oldest belief systems had to do with life after death. Many of us believe we have had contact with the Other Side through the deaths of loved ones. I had a profound experience in this regard, became very religious (Christian) and I have been a strong influence on friends seeking religion. That said, I had a deep spiritual crisis last year and dug ever deeper into religious history, etc. I feel I get greater understanding by listening to rabbis. One of them described knowledge and faith in G-d comes from humans contemplating, basically, infinity and the intensity of knowing that there is something very big, powerful and knowledgeable beyond us and our understanding. This rabbi also defined the Garden of Eden as describing human spirits in a sort of pre-existence, seeking knowledge which was a good thing in this telling. (I do not know if these are Kabbalistic beliefs or regular Judaism.) Some recent research has suggested that some ¬®gods¬®, for instance Greek gods, may have been actual people. While I do not agree with everything Graham Hancock puts forth, I think he has a strong point that humanity has basic amnesia with only slight and fabled memories, of a tremendous cataclysm in the past. He suggests comet strikes on the earth causing a rapid meltdown of the last ice age which brought on global floods. Perhaps part of religion is humanity trying to remember, some 12,000 years later, an un-explainable something that nearly wiped out life on earth. Finally, there are oddballs like me who have neurological conditions that cause us to have experiences with altered consciousness. My personal issue is chronic migraine and it causes me to occasionally see shadow people or animals. I know they do not exist but if I did, perhaps I would think to start my own religion. While understanding none of that is real. I DID have an out of body experience where I saw an event happening. I can actually prove this one but do not want to give the details here. I am not being coy. There is an ongoing criminal investigation. After that original experience, I occasionally have psychic experiences and know things before they happen. There seems to be an interconnectedness in the universe, in this dimension and perhaps in and to others. I believe the ancients and up to primitive societies of today, can feel and sense this thing to which quantum physics points but of which most of us have no understanding.
